#Parallax Nexus (#1085, "cards never returned to hand") - PARKED:
#Cannot reach the return leg: the activated exile grants the TARGETED OPPONENT a
#chooser over their own hand (ability$!...target(*|myhand)!$ targetedplayer) during
#MY turn, and that chooser wedges - the opponent's hand click is not accepted (with
#or without source-reclick confirm) and every subsequent command is swallowed.
#Same family as Hollow Specter / the opponent-chooser-on-my-turn gap. Re-probe after
#the chooser-ownership round; the return-on-leave leg (the actual complaint) is
#untested until then.
[INIT]
firstmain
[PLAYER1]
manapool:{1}{W}
inplay:parallax nexus
hand:disenchant
[PLAYER2]
hand:hill giant
[DO]
parallax nexus
choice 0
p2
goto firstmain
goto firstmain
hill giant
goto firstmain
goto firstmain
disenchant
parallax nexus
goto firstmain
goto firstmain
[ASSERT]
FIRSTMAIN
[PLAYER1]
graveyard:disenchant,parallax nexus
[PLAYER2]
hand:hill giant
[END]
